## Summary
- allow owner-scoped live transcript hits to fall back to synthetic session keys when the combined session store has no entry
- keep the fallback scoped to the transcript owner/current agent so cross-agent live orphan hits still fail closed
- apply the same resolution path to memory-core search filtering and memory-wiki session path checks

## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)

- Behavior or issue addressed: live transcript search hits with paths like `sessions/<agent>/<uuid>.jsonl` were dropped when the combined session store had no metadata entry, even when the hit belongs to the requesting/scoped agent.
- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout from this PR branch on Linux, commit `a4766db00e` (`fix/live-session-orphan-visibility`), using the repo's installed `node_modules` and `node --import tsx` against the actual patched source file.
- Exact steps or command run after this patch: ran a live Node smoke script from the repository root importing `./src/plugin-sdk/session-transcript-hit.ts`, simulating an empty combined session store and three real session-hit path shapes: same-agent owner-scoped, cross-agent owner-scoped, and legacy basename-only.
- Evidence after fix (copied live terminal output):

```text
$ node --import tsx --input-type=module <<'EOF'
import { extractTranscriptIdentityFromSessionsMemoryHit, resolveTranscriptStemToSessionKeys } from './src/plugin-sdk/session-transcript-hit.ts';

const cases = [
  { label: 'same-agent owner-scoped live orphan', path: 'sessions/main/live-orphan-after-fix.jsonl', scopedAgentId: 'main' },
  { label: 'cross-agent owner-scoped live orphan', path: 'sessions/peer/live-orphan-after-fix.jsonl', scopedAgentId: 'main' },
  { label: 'legacy basename-only live orphan', path: 'sessions/live-orphan-after-fix.jsonl', scopedAgentId: 'main' },
];

for (const c of cases) {
  const identity = extractTranscriptIdentityFromSessionsMemoryHit(c.path);
  const ownerMatchesScope = Boolean(identity?.ownerAgentId && identity.ownerAgentId === c.scopedAgentId);
  const keys = identity
    ? resolveTranscriptStemToSessionKeys({
        store: {},
        stem: identity.stem,
        ...(ownerMatchesScope ? { ownerAgentId: identity.ownerAgentId } : {}),
      })
    : [];
  console.log(`${c.label}: path=${c.path}`);
  console.log(`  parsed=${JSON.stringify(identity)}`);
  console.log(`  empty-store keys=${JSON.stringify(keys)}`);
  console.log(`  visible-to-${c.scopedAgentId}=${keys.includes(`agent:${c.scopedAgentId}:live-orphan-after-fix`)}`);
}
EOF
same-agent owner-scoped live orphan: path=sessions/main/live-orphan-after-fix.jsonl
  parsed={"stem":"live-orphan-after-fix","ownerAgentId":"main","archived":false}
  empty-store keys=["agent:main:live-orphan-after-fix"]
  visible-to-main=true
cross-agent owner-scoped live orphan: path=sessions/peer/live-orphan-after-fix.jsonl
  parsed={"stem":"live-orphan-after-fix","ownerAgentId":"peer","archived":false}
  empty-store keys=[]
  visible-to-main=false
legacy basename-only live orphan: path=sessions/live-orphan-after-fix.jsonl
  parsed={"stem":"live-orphan-after-fix","archived":false}
  empty-store keys=[]
  visible-to-main=false
```

- Observed result after fix: same-agent `sessions/main/*.jsonl` orphan hits produce the synthetic key `agent:main:<stem>` from owner metadata, while cross-agent and legacy basename-only orphan hits still produce no fallback key.
- What was not tested: a full long-running OpenClaw gateway with an embedding index refresh and UI search interaction.
- Proof limitations or environment constraints: this is a local runtime smoke using the actual patched OpenClaw source and live Node execution, not a screenshot/recording; unit/regression tests below cover the memory-core and memory-wiki consumers around the same helper behavior.
- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): prior code only synthesized keys from `archivedOwnerAgentId`, so a live owner-scoped path with an empty store returned no keys and was filtered out.

## Tests
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugin-sdk/session-transcript-hit.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/session-search-visibility.test.ts`
- `git diff --check`

Fixes the live `sessions/<agent>/<uuid>.jsonl` orphan variant related to #53550, #73471, #76452, and #83518.
